            <h5>Before You Measure</h5>
            <p class="ceg-b32">...round up all the tools you need:</p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li><strong>Measuring tape:</strong> A fabric version is best to get the most accurate measurement.</li>
                <li><strong>Pen & paper:</strong> To record your measurements.</li>
                <li><strong>Mirror:</strong> Standing in front of a mirror while taking your measurements will make easier to ensure you’re measuring the correct areas.</li>
                <li><strong>Non-padded bra:</strong> Make sure it reflects your true shape.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>How to Measure Your Band Size</h5>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li>Measure around your rib cage directly below your bust.</li>
                <li>The tape measure should be evenly horizontal and not pulled tightly.</li>
                <li>Round the measurement to the nearest whole number.</li>
                <li>If the measurement is an even number add 4”.</li>
                <li>If the measurement is an odd number add 5”.</li>
                <li>The total is your band size.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>How to Measure Your Cup Size</h5>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li>Measure the fullest part of your bust while wearing a non-padded bra.</li>
                <li>Subtract the band measurement from the bust measurement.</li>
                <li>The difference equals your cup size.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
