        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>How to choose a nursing bra?</h5>
            <p class="ceg-b32">Pick a nursing bra based on what you find most comfortable, your level of activity and your favorite styles. The best maternity bras that expertly blend fashion (think embellished details) with function (breathable fabrics) are the way to go. We’ve rounded up top-notch nursing bra styles you and baby are sure to love.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>What nursing bra can I wear on casual days?</h5>
            <p class="ceg-b32">From full-coverage to demi-cup styles, there are plenty of maternity bras to choose from. For unwavering support, stock up on underwire bras in your new size.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>Can I sleep in my nursing bra?</h5>
            <p class="ceg-b32">You can sleep in your nursing bra if that feels comfortable for you. Soft and lightweight, wrap bras or sleep bras provide light support and ensure effortless nighttime nursing access. Crafted with a simple pullover design, wrap-style bras are ideal for overnight comfort.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>What bra can I workout in while pregnant?</h5>
            <p class="ceg-b32">Depending on doctor's orders, you may get the go-ahead to stay active during your pregnancy—or maybe you just love the sporty look. Either way, sports bras and racerback bras will serve you well. They'll help keep your support needs covered during pregnancy, after the baby is born and throughout the entire nursing period.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>Can I wear a wireless nursing bra?</h5>
            <p class="ceg-b32">Yes, you can if you’re looking for the ultimate comfort with flexible fit. A wireless nursing bra is perfect! They come in a variety of styles designed for easy nursing.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>What style bra can help make nursing easier?</h5>
            <p class="ceg-b32">Clip-down bras make nursing super-easy with clips at each strap for quick access. Plus, this versatile design offers great support throughout the day. Those 3 A.M. feedings will (hopefully) become easier.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>What bra should I wear during my first trimester?</h5>
            <p class="ceg-b32">Typically, your breasts will grow quickly during this time. It’s smart to invest in stretchy and seamless bras you can use throughout different breast sizes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>What bra should I wear during my second trimester?</h5>
            <p class="ceg-b32">In most cases, your ribcage will start to expand during this stage and your breast growth will start to slow down. Pick bras that provide extra support, have flexible underwires and secure closures.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>What bra should I wear during my third trimester?</h5>
            <p class="ceg-b32">This is when you should have reached your nursing bra size. Stock up on your favorite styles including clip-down, full-figure and flexible options.</p>
